          "date": "2017-04-18 00:06:02.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-18 21:01:49.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: Fix discovery threading",
        "message": "LU-9119 lnet: Fix discovery threading\n\nDiscovery shouldn't block the thread which is currently processing\na message. This thread is an LND scheduler thread, which also\nservices transmits. If discovery blocks it then it opens the window\nfor the scenario where a ping initiated by discovery also placed\non the blocked LND scheduler thread queue. The LND scheduler\nwill never wake up to service that ping and therefore discovery\nwill never complete.\n\nAdded a non-blocking mode for discovery exercised from\nlnet_select_pathway(). In this mode discovery request is queued\non the discovery thread and then returns right away. The message\nis then queued on a pending queue for the peer. When discovery\ncompletes the pending queue is visited and if discovery was\nsuccessful then messages are sent out to their targets, otherwise\nlnet_finalize() is called with the returned error.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I172dfaa95ded35a45d8b70a78b9268ac96b6081c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
